accessibility.title: Accessibility
accessibility.description: These checks highlight opportunities to [improve the accessibility of your web app](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility). Only a subset of accessibility issues can be automatically detected so manual testing is also encouraged.
accessibility.manualDescription: These items address areas which an automated testing tool cannot cover. Learn more in our guide on [conducting an accessibility review](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility/how-to-review).

Technologies.Name: Javascript
Technologies.Description: JavaScript is a scripting language most often used for client-side web development.

Technologies.Name: UTF-8
Technologies.Description: UTF-8 (8-bit UCS/Unicode Transformation Format) is a variable-length character encoding for Unicode. It is the preferred encoding for web pages.

Technologies.Name: Cascading Style Sheets
Technologies.Description: Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in a markup language. Its most common application is to style web pages written in HTML

Technologies.Name: ISO/IEC 8859
Technologies.Description: ISO 8859, more formally ISO/IEC 8859, is a joint ISO and IEC standard for 8-bit character encodings for use by computers. The standard is divided into numbered, separately published parts, such as ISO/IEC 8859-1, ISO/IEC 8859-2, etc., each of which may be informally referred to as a standard in itself. There are currently 15 parts as of 2006 excluding the abandoned ISO/IEC 8859-12 standard.

Technologies.Name: HTML 5 Specific Tags
Technologies.Description: This page contains tags that are specific to an HTML 5 implementation.

Technologies.Name: IFrame
Technologies.Description: The page shows content with an iframe; an embedded frame that loads another webpage.

Technologies.Name: Google Analytics
Technologies.Description: Google Analytics offers a host of compelling features and benefits for everyone from senior executives and advertising and marketing professionals to site owners and content developers.

Technologies.Name: Google Analytics Classic
Technologies.Description: Classic Google Analytics - sites that are using non-universal analytics code.

Technologies.Name: PHP
Technologies.Description: PHP is a widely used general-purpose scripting language that is especially suited for Web development and can be embedded into HTML.

Technologies.Name: Content Security Policy
Technologies.Description: Content Security Policy is a computer security concept, to prevent cross-site scripting XSS attacks.

Technologies.Name: Apache
Technologies.Description: Apache has been the most popular web server on the Internet since April 1996.

Technologies.Name: Red Hat Enterprise Linux
Technologies.Description: Red Hat Enterprise Linux (often abbreviated to RHEL) is a Linux distribution produced by Red Hat and targeted toward the commercial market, including mainframes.

Technologies.Name: nginx
Technologies.Description: nginx [engine x] is a HTTP server and mail proxy server written by Igor Sysoev.
